The City of Tshwane says roaming water tankers have been dispatched to ensure a continuous supply of drinking water. JOHANNESBURG - The City of Tshwane has sent a team of experts to conduct urgent tests in the Greater Hammanskraal area following a suspected cholera outbreak. It says roaming water tankers have been dispatched to ensure a continuous supply of drinking water. The city's Selby Bokaba says they will inform affected residents of the results as soon as they are made available. “We received information that there’s a possible outbreak of cholera in the Greater Hammanskraal area, we subsequently sent our team from the laboratory section.”